Instructions:

0) make sure to have installed schedtoold (make; make install)
1) copy sched to /etc/init.d/schedtoold
2) edit /etc/schedtoold.conf to your needs (example found in this archive)
3) start it via /etc/init.d/schedtoold start
4) if you want it to be started at bootup run "rc-update add schedtoold default"


